gomodel:SYNGO_4636  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3. Vezatin knock-down induces less dendritic branching complexity in vitro.\n\nFigure 5. light microscopy shows a decrease in spines in a knockout mouse model that depleted Vezatin expression in forebrain.. Experimental description: \"To generate conditional Vezatin-deficient mice, Veztfl/fl were crossed with transgenic mice that express cre recombinase under the control of the calcium/calmodulin-dependent kinase II α subunit of the CamKII promoter (Casanova et al., 2001).\"\n\n\"Primary neuronal culture, immunostaining, and confocal analysis of spines.\nCulture and immunostaining of hippocampal neurons from E18.5 mouse embryos were adapted from Danglot et al. (2003).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4636" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

